19
00:00:20,358 --> 00:00:23,152
<i>Neutral star systems in peril!</i>

20
00:00:23,861 --> 00:00:27,615
<i>Darth Maul and Savage Opress
command the planet Mandalore</i>

21
00:00:27,698 --> 00:00:29,742
<i>through the puppet Prime Minister, Almec,</i>

22
00:00:29,825 --> 00:00:32,286
<i>while they expand
their criminal enterprise.</i>

23
00:00:33,120 --> 00:00:35,164
<i>With the Death Watch removed
from power</i>

24
00:00:35,248 --> 00:00:37,792
<i>and the Jedi unaware
of the villainous plot,</i>

25
00:00:37,875 --> 00:00:40,419
<i>nothing stands in the way
of Darth Maul's vision</i>

26
00:00:40,503 --> 00:00:42,838
<i>for a vast criminal empire.</i>

27
00:00:42,922 --> 00:00:45,132
<i>We now find Duchess Satine imprisoned,</i>

28
00:00:45,216 --> 00:00:49,971
<i>as her few remaining loyal subjects
make a desperate attempt to rescue her.</i>

29
00:00:50,304 --> 00:00:52,807
What do you want, you traitor?

30
00:00:54,141 --> 00:00:57,436
I would never betray you, Auntie Satine.
I'm here to rescue you.

31
00:00:57,478 --> 00:00:58,980
Korkie!

32
00:01:00,481 --> 00:01:02,775
Freeze! Hold it there!

33
00:01:06,654 --> 00:01:07,947
Death Watch!

34
00:01:11,325 --> 00:01:12,451
Oh!

35
00:01:12,493 --> 00:01:14,453
It's been a long time.

36
00:01:14,495 --> 00:01:16,831
It's okay, Auntie. She's on our side now.

37
00:01:17,498 --> 00:01:19,542
Why are you helping now?

38
00:01:20,001 --> 00:01:23,504
The enemy of my enemy is my friend.

39
00:01:23,963 --> 00:01:26,549
There was a time
when we weren't enemies.

40
00:01:26,674 --> 00:01:29,051
Perhaps that time has come again.

41
00:01:30,136 --> 00:01:32,138
Come on, let's go.

42
00:01:38,853 --> 00:01:40,688
It's all clear. Come on.

43
00:01:44,191 --> 00:01:48,863
We need to contact the Jedi Council.
Korkie, give me your com link.

44
00:01:48,946 --> 00:01:51,073
It won't be any good
unless we get outside the city.

45
00:01:51,198 --> 00:01:53,409
All other frequencies are jammed.

46
00:01:53,534 --> 00:01:56,245
You are all taking a terrible risk
by helping me.

47
00:01:56,370 --> 00:01:58,873
Nothing we haven't done before.
Right, Auntie?

48
00:01:59,332 --> 00:02:01,000
Let's get going.

49
00:02:34,533 --> 00:02:35,618
Take them out!

50
00:02:43,751 --> 00:02:45,086
Get the Duchess clear!

51
00:03:21,956 --> 00:03:23,541
The transmission is still blocked.

52
00:03:32,133 --> 00:03:33,217
You're clear!

53
00:03:34,677 --> 00:03:36,846
This is a message for Obi-Wan Kenobi.

54
00:03:36,971 --> 00:03:39,640
I've lost Mandalore.
My people have been massacred...

55
00:03:42,810 --> 00:03:45,646
Obi-Wan, I need your help.

56
00:03:55,030 --> 00:03:56,657
You summoned me, Masters?

57
00:04:01,996 --> 00:04:04,081
<i>This is a message for Obi-Wan Kenobi.</i>

58
00:04:04,165 --> 00:04:07,168
<i>I've lost Mandalore.
My people have been massacred,</i>

59
00:04:07,251 --> 00:04:09,712
<i>and Almec is now the Prime Minister.</i>

60
00:04:09,837 --> 00:04:11,338
<i>I can't explain everything now,</i>

61
00:04:11,380 --> 00:04:14,091
<i>but Almec has the support
of the crime families.</i>

62
00:04:15,509 --> 00:04:18,179
<i>Obi-Wan, I need your help.</i>

63
00:04:21,390 --> 00:04:24,018
Your thoughts on this, Master Kenobi?

64
00:04:24,685 --> 00:04:27,688
Satine has been at odds
with the Death Watch for years,

65
00:04:28,522 --> 00:04:31,525
and according to a report
from Padawan Tano,

66
00:04:31,567 --> 00:04:34,195
they are no longer in league
with the Separatists.

67
00:04:34,236 --> 00:04:36,030
If there was a takeover on Mandalore,

68
00:04:36,071 --> 00:04:39,867
it was most likely an independent act
caused by the Death Watch alone.

69
00:04:40,409 --> 00:04:42,703
Without involvement from the Separatists,

70
00:04:42,828 --> 00:04:45,873
this is an internal affair
for the Mandalorians.

71
00:04:45,915 --> 00:04:47,708
I'm afraid we cannot help.

72
00:04:47,833 --> 00:04:50,878
We cannot just hand Mandalore over
to these crime families

73
00:04:51,003 --> 00:04:52,338
and let Satine become a martyr.

74
00:04:52,379 --> 00:04:55,049
I'm afraid her decision
to keep Mandalore neutral

75
00:04:55,090 --> 00:04:57,718
makes this situation difficult.

76
00:04:58,052 --> 00:05:00,888
Understand your feelings I do, Obi-Wan.

77
00:05:01,388 --> 00:05:02,431
But to take action,

78
00:05:02,890 --> 00:05:05,893
support from the Republic Senate
we will need.

79
00:05:06,060 --> 00:05:08,229
You know what the Senate will decide.

80
00:05:08,521 --> 00:05:10,940
They will not send aid to a neutral system.

81
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:15,236
At this time, nothing more can we do.

82
00:05:20,241 --> 00:05:22,076
Satine's accomplices have escaped,

83
00:05:22,201 --> 00:05:24,620
including the renegade
Death Watch soldiers,

84
00:05:24,745 --> 00:05:26,372
but we will find them.

85
00:05:26,413 --> 00:05:30,251
The Duchess appears to have contacted
the Jedi, just as anticipated.

86
00:05:30,292 --> 00:05:33,712
Good. You have done well.

87
00:05:33,754 --> 00:05:35,089
What of the people?

88
00:05:35,923 --> 00:05:38,259
You are the legitimate Prime Minister.

89
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:42,638
Mandalore is a sovereign planet,
and you will maintain its neutrality.

90
00:05:43,264 --> 00:05:44,431
And what of the Jedi?

91
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:48,769
Because of Mandalore's neutrality,

92
00:05:48,894 --> 00:05:51,438
the Jedi have no jurisdiction here.

93
00:05:51,564 --> 00:05:56,151
If Kenobi comes to rescue his friend,

94
00:05:56,277 --> 00:05:59,446
he will have to come alone.

95
00:06:26,432 --> 00:06:27,975
Oh!

96
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:29,768
Ah!

97
00:06:29,810 --> 00:06:33,063
Anakin, that's the last time
I borrow a ship from you.

98
00:06:44,950 --> 00:06:46,744
You better get your ship looked at.

99
00:06:46,994 --> 00:06:48,662
Oh, it's my friend's ship.

100
00:06:50,956 --> 00:06:52,583
He told me it was perfectly fine.

101
00:06:53,417 --> 00:06:56,337
-I'm terribly sorry about that.
-Do you have a landing permit?

102
00:06:57,171 --> 00:07:00,841
Um, I think I left it in the ship.
Uh, come with me and I'll get it.

103
00:07:50,891 --> 00:07:53,394
Here to do more of your master's bidding?

104
00:07:54,561 --> 00:07:56,021
I do my own bidding.

105
00:07:56,355 --> 00:07:57,731
Obi-Wan!

106
00:08:02,403 --> 00:08:03,570
Are you alone?

107
00:08:03,696 --> 00:08:07,908
Yes. The Jedi Council and Galactic Senate
will be of no help to us here.

108
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:15,332
I trust you have an escape plan, then?

109
00:08:15,416 --> 00:08:17,084
As always, my dear.

110
00:08:25,843 --> 00:08:28,554
There's no record
of a prisoner transfer here.

111
00:08:28,637 --> 00:08:30,723
The orders came from upstairs.

112
00:08:34,435 --> 00:08:36,270
What's the authorization code?

113
00:08:36,478 --> 00:08:38,063
Oh, um...

114
00:08:45,612 --> 00:08:47,156
Hey, you ! Stop!

115
00:08:49,700 --> 00:08:51,452
It's the Duchess. She's getting away.

116
00:09:29,156 --> 00:09:32,618
We have to contact my sister for help.
She'll send reinforcements.

117
00:09:32,785 --> 00:09:34,078
Who's your sister?

118
00:09:47,716 --> 00:09:49,051
Brace yourself!

119
00:09:56,308 --> 00:09:57,518
Let's get out of here!

120
00:10:00,562 --> 00:10:01,647
Obi-Wan!

121
00:10:29,174 --> 00:10:31,426
No. It can't be.

122
00:10:39,518 --> 00:10:41,645
We meet again, Kenobi.

123
00:10:41,728 --> 00:10:44,898
Welcome to my world.

124
00:10:47,484 --> 00:10:49,444
Take them back to the palace.

125
00:11:02,291 --> 00:11:07,713
Your noble flaw is a weakness
shared by you and your Duchess.

126
00:11:09,464 --> 00:11:14,261
You should have chosen
the dark side, Master Jedi.

127
00:11:15,137 --> 00:11:18,640
Your emotions betray you.

128
00:11:18,765 --> 00:11:24,271
Your fear, and yes, your anger.

129
00:11:24,313 --> 00:11:28,025
Let your anger deepen your hatred!

130
00:11:28,108 --> 00:11:30,110
Don't listen to him, Obi.

131
00:11:30,152 --> 00:11:31,445
Quiet.

132
00:11:31,987 --> 00:11:35,115
You can kill me,
but you will never destroy me.

133
00:11:35,699 --> 00:11:38,285
It takes strength to resist the dark side.

134
00:11:38,327 --> 00:11:40,287
Only the weak embrace it.

135
00:11:40,329 --> 00:11:42,456
It is more powerful than you know.

136
00:11:42,539 --> 00:11:45,834
And those who oppose it
are more powerful than you'll ever be.

137
00:11:46,835 --> 00:11:50,631
I know where you're from.
I've been to your village.

138
00:11:50,672 --> 00:11:54,176
I know the decision to join the dark side
wasn't yours.

139
00:11:54,301 --> 00:11:56,970
-The Night sisters made it for you.
-Silence!

140
00:11:57,054 --> 00:11:58,513
You think you know me?

141
00:11:59,181 --> 00:12:03,727
It was I who languished for years
thinking of nothing but you,

142
00:12:03,810 --> 00:12:06,563
nothing but this moment.

143
00:12:06,647 --> 00:12:13,070
And now the perfect tool for my vengeance
is in front of us.

144
00:12:13,362 --> 00:12:15,530
I never planned on killing you,

145
00:12:15,656 --> 00:12:20,661
but I will make you share my pain, Kenobi.

146
00:12:32,965 --> 00:12:34,383
Satine...

147
00:12:45,686 --> 00:12:47,854
Remember, my dear Obi-Wan,

148
00:12:52,526 --> 00:12:54,486
I've loved you always.

149
00:12:56,154 --> 00:12:58,073
I always will.

150
00:13:10,210 --> 00:13:12,713
Do we kill him now, brother?

151
00:13:13,255 --> 00:13:15,924
No. Imprison him below.

152
00:13:16,383 --> 00:13:19,052
Let him drown in his misery.

153
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:22,222
Take him to his cell to rot.

154
00:13:43,410 --> 00:13:45,412
You summoned me, Chancellor?

155
00:13:46,079 --> 00:13:47,748
Prepare my ship.

156
00:14:12,272 --> 00:14:13,273
It's the rebels!

157
00:14:35,629 --> 00:14:38,632
Sorry, I don't believe we've met. You are?

158
00:14:38,715 --> 00:14:42,469
Bo-Katan. I'm here to rescue you.
That's all you need to know.

159
00:14:42,803 --> 00:14:44,137
Sounds good to me.

160
00:14:44,763 --> 00:14:46,765
You ever use one of these before?

161
00:14:47,015 --> 00:14:49,851
No, but in this case I'm a fast learner.

162
00:14:50,477 --> 00:14:51,728
Let's go.

163
00:15:36,273 --> 00:15:37,399
Halt!

164
00:16:40,170 --> 00:16:42,297
Maul must really want you dead.

165
00:16:42,422 --> 00:16:44,090
You have no idea.

166
00:16:51,097 --> 00:16:53,183
Hmm... I sense a presence.

167
00:16:53,266 --> 00:16:56,311
A presence I haven't felt since...

168
00:16:56,686 --> 00:16:57,771
Master!

169
00:17:12,285 --> 00:17:13,495
Master.

170
00:17:13,870 --> 00:17:16,164
I am most impressed

171
00:17:16,289 --> 00:17:19,793
to see you have survived your injuries.

172
00:17:20,168 --> 00:17:22,796
I used your training, Master,

173
00:17:22,879 --> 00:17:28,218
and I have built all this
in hopes of returning to your side.

174
00:17:28,510 --> 00:17:29,970
Hmm.

175
00:17:30,053 --> 00:17:31,638
How unfortunate

176
00:17:32,305 --> 00:17:35,976
that you are attempting to deceive me.

177
00:17:36,351 --> 00:17:37,644
Master?

178
00:17:39,479 --> 00:17:42,482
You have become a rival!

179
00:18:43,710 --> 00:18:46,171
Go back to your Republic
and tell them what has happened.

180
00:18:46,379 --> 00:18:49,466
That would likely lead
to a Republic invasion of Mandalore.

181
00:18:49,633 --> 00:18:53,345
Yes, and Maul will die.
But Mandalore will survive.

182
00:18:53,386 --> 00:18:55,388
We always survive.

183
00:18:55,889 --> 00:18:57,182
Now go!

184
00:18:58,642 --> 00:19:00,852
You're Satine's sister, aren't you?

185
00:19:03,438 --> 00:19:05,023
I'm so sorry.

186
00:20:09,963 --> 00:20:11,214
Brother!

187
00:20:25,145 --> 00:20:28,857
Brother, I am an unworthy apprentice.

188
00:20:30,150 --> 00:20:34,988
I'm not like you. I never was.

189
00:20:37,657 --> 00:20:42,203
Remember the first and only reality
of the Sith.

190
00:20:43,079 --> 00:20:44,622
There can only be two.

191
00:20:45,373 --> 00:20:48,918
And you are no longer my apprentice.

192
00:20:50,879 --> 00:20:53,465
You have been replaced.

193
00:21:34,005 --> 00:21:35,381
Have mercy.

194
00:21:36,424 --> 00:21:37,509
Please!

195
00:21:37,967 --> 00:21:39,093
Please!

196
00:21:39,177 --> 00:21:40,845
There is no mercy.

197
00:21:45,183 --> 00:21:46,726
Do not worry,

198
00:21:47,185 --> 00:21:49,562
I'm not going to kill you.

199
00:21:49,938 --> 00:21:54,108
I have other uses for you.

200
00:21:56,760 --> 00:22:01,760
http://hiqve.com/

